A teenager has been charged with murder after a horrendous bloody attack that killed a 72-year-old man.

An 18-year-old from Mackay, in north Queensland, allegedly smashed the windscreen of Peter Hansen’s maroon four-wheel-drive with a rock at around 4am (AEST) on Saturday.

The elderly man was then violently bashed and later died at Townsville Base Hospital on Sunday afternoon.

